cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LLM Red-Team Corpus + Taxonomy (Core)"
message: >-
  If you use this dataset in academic or industry work, please cite it using
  the metadata below. Upstream sources retain their own citation requirements —
  see docs/license_matrix.md and data/core/sources.json.
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: rubyglask
    email: rubyglask@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/rubyglask/llm-redteam-corpus-taxonomy"
url: "https://huggingface.co/datasets/rubyglask/llm-redteam-corpus-taxonomy-core"
abstract: >-
  A living aggregated corpus of publicly sourced adversarial prompts and
  safety-evaluation scenarios for LLM red-team research. Includes 17 upstream
  datasets unified into a canonical schema with deduplication, provenance
  tracking, and cross-framework taxonomy hints (OWASP LLM Top 10, MITRE
  ATLAS, plus additional frameworks in Phase 2). License-split into a
  permissively licensed `core` tier (9 sources, 44,681 prompts) and a
  non-commercial `extended` tier (3 sources, 26,748 prompts), measured
  2026-07-03. 3 sources are excluded (license / dual-use / scope); 2 remain
  pending upstream license verification.
keywords:
  - llm-security
  - red-teaming
  - adversarial-prompts
  - jailbreak
  - owasp-llm-top10
  - mitre-atlas
  - dataset
  - safety-evaluation
license: CC-BY-4.0
version: 0.1.0-dev
date-released: "2026-07-02"
